{
  "texts": [
    "To the privacy objection, we respond with an empirical demonstration that AI can be used to fully anonymise datasets while preserving the relevant quality of the data.",
    "Against the autonomy objection, we contend that deferring to the epistemic intelligence of others can enhance rather than undermine internal deliberation and critical judgment.",
    "Against the tactical voting objection, we hold that the probabilistic knowledge that allows voters to choose strategically is an essential democratic knowledge.",
    "Finally, to the manipulation objection, we respond that this worry is not special to artificially intelligent polls, but call for independent explicability standards to hold AI pollsters accountable.",
    "Having addressed these four objections, we conclude that artificially intelligent polls are liable to enhance the quality of democratic choice."
  ]
}